snippet.textDisplay: People complaining about the authenticity being lost must appreciate that all music evolves. Even pure indian classical music has changed. We have ragas influenced by the middle east too. (I know video is semi-classical, not pure). Who are you to judge what sounds good to others? Some people here have a true hatred for the use of western music, as though western music cannot have 'ruhaniat', as if it cannot add to the bliss. If you want 'pure' sufi, then go listen to it elsewhere.
